Over 100 shacks were destroyed in the blaze on Saturday night which was believed to have been started intentionally said EMS spokesperson Robert Mulaudzi. Allegations are that it was a deliberate arson attack as there had been some people fighting in the area Mulaudzi said. This will form part of the investigations. Mulaudzi did not immediately have details on the two casualties only mentioning that it was two adult males.Meanwhile some of the locals had already started rebuilding their shacks on Sunday morning.